snippet.textDisplay: My prayers are with everyone involved with this. This tragedy hits so close to home for me, that listening to this brought tears to my eyes. I recently lost my fiance in an unexpected way, as well as losing my mother, brother and unborn child. The pain of loss is felt so deeply and for so long, by loved ones who are left behind, but we have to always try to stay positive, to just keep putting one foot ahead of the next, holding our heads up high, and never forgetting how to smile, because our loved ones would certainly want us to keep loving life and making as many positive changes as possible in the world around us. As long as all the families involved here are able to just stay strong, then time will help them to heal. They will all be in my prayers💜

snippet.textDisplay: Yes, it is sad that Kobe Byant and his daughter Gianna died in the crash, but so did 7 other people who mattered to a whole lot of other people in the world. They all touched people in unique ways all through there lives whether they were famous or not, whether they were 41, 56, or 13. And these were the other 7 who deserve mention just as much as Kobe & Gianna, baseball coach John Altobelli, his wife, Keri, and their basketball-playing daughter Alyssa; mother and daughter Sarah and Payton Chester; Mamba Academy basketball coach Christina Mauser; and pilot Ara Zobayan. And now scores of people are mourning Kobe and his daughter, while scores of people are mourning these 7. When you go to HEAVEN and you get your Angel Wings, I am sure there isn't a special section for the famous, they are all the same and GOD BLESS EACH AND EVERY SINGLE ONE OF THEM. May they Rest In Peace!
